  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6767 sitting above the GEX flip at 6756 in PIN regime, dealers are currently long gamma and will sell any rally toward the massive +7916M wall at 6800 while providing buying support on dips. The sharp -26.5% and -37.6% GEX declines over 1-5 minutes combined with the wall break event suggests recent heavy gamma positioning shifts, likely creating temporary instability before the PIN stabilization mechanics reassert. Key levels to watch: 6765 negative gamma cluster (-5947M) as the downside amplification zone and 6800 as the major resistance wall where dealer selling intensifies.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect choppy price action with a magnet pull toward 6800 but strong selling pressure capping upside there.",
